summary: Derrick Henry, the star running back for the Baltimore Ravens, has been making headlines recently. He tied the NFL record set by Jim Brown, helping the Ravens secure the AFC North title on his 31st birthday. Henry is projected to have a strong performance against the Cleveland Browns in Week 18, with experts predicting high points and stats. There has been speculation about Henry's potential to reach 2,000 rushing yards this season, but he has not yet commented on the possibility. Despite being selected to the Pro Bowl, Henry has remained reserved in his response. His non-expressive demeanor has been a topic of discussion, with some speculating about his reasons for not expressing more excitement. Additionally, injury updates have shed light on Henry's availability for the Browns game, but no definitive status has been given.

summary: Derrick Rose, a former Chicago Bulls MVP, was honored with a special night in his celebration. The team announced plans to retire his jersey during the 2025-26 NBA season. In addition to the jersey retirement, Rose opened a one-day flower shop to interact with fans and give away free roses. During the celebration, Rose emphasized that the tribute was not just for him but for the entire city of Chicago where he grew up. Despite his accomplishments, Rose expressed his reluctance to have a statue created due to the recent controversial depictions of athletes. Despite this, Rose's pop-up flower shop drew a large crowd in downtown Chicago, underscoring his enduring popularity among Bulls fans.

name: Sonny Smart
summary: Tragedy has struck the Georgia football community with the passing of Sonny Smart, the father of head coach Kirby Smart. Sonny Smart passed away after sustaining a fall in New Orleans on New Year's Eve, just hours before Georgia faced Notre Dame in the Sugar Bowl. The news of his death has sent shockwaves through the football world and beyond. Sonny Smart was a well-respected high school football coach in Georgia for many years. His son, Kirby, has established himself as one of the top college football coaches in the nation, leading Georgia to a national championship in 2021. The Smart family and the entire Georgia Bulldogs community are mourning the loss of their beloved father and coach.

name: Ed Pettifer
summary: A British citizen with alleged ties to the royal family has been identified as a victim in a deadly New Year's Day attack in New Orleans. The man killed has been identified as Edward Pettifer, the stepson of Tiggy Legge-Bourke, who was the former nanny to Princes William and Harry. Prince William has expressed shock and sadness at the news. The royal family has paid tribute to Pettifer, acknowledging his connection to the family. The attack, which occurred on Bourbon Street, claimed multiple lives, including Pettifer's. His death has drawn attention due to his family's association with the British monarchy.

summary: Russell Wilson's injury status is uncertain for the Steelers' Week 18 game against the Bengals, raising concerns about his status as the team's starting quarterback. Amidst the team's struggles, Wilson has faced criticism, including comparisons to his backup, Kenny Pickett, and a claim by a former Pro Bowl wide receiver that he is "not very good." Despite the speculation, Wilson has urged his teammates to move past their recent losses and focus on their upcoming game. Meanwhile, reports suggest that the Steelers are considering signing a former $128 million quarterback as Wilson's backup. As the Steelers prepare to face the Bengals, the focus remains on Wilson's performance and the team's overall trajectory.
